About this item

  • Compact 2.1CH Dolby Atmos Soundbar - Enhance your home theater experience with the HiElite A21 dolby atmos soundbar designed for smart TVs, bringing movies, music, and more to life like never before with Dolby Atmos' precise sound positioning technology. (Note: This batch of soundbars does not support the memory function. If you would like to use this feature, we have customized the firmware for use whenever needed.)
  • 3D Spatial Audio and Dolby Atmos - Experience audio like never before with 3D Spatial Audio powered by Dolby Atmos sound bars for TV. This technology offers an immersive three-dimensional sound experience that transcends traditional surround sound systems. Get lost in theater-like sound from your favorite content with Spatial Audio. Music and movies available in Dolby Atmos deliver full immersion with 360-degree surround sound.
  • Crafted with High-quality Materials - Using high-end aluminum-magnesium alloy diaphragms, the system's lightweight design and high rigidity ensure optimal sound quality, providing excellent sensitivity and durability. Each driver is equipped with high quality copper rings to reduce interference and improve signal clarity. The sound bar for smart TV minimize distortion and stabilize the magnetic field to ensure a balanced and precise sound.
  • Hiwill HarmonicX Sound Processing - HXS-Processing ClearVoice: Our next-generation sound processing technology for crystal-clear vocals. Through superior materials and Hiwill's exclusive HarmonicX Sound Processing. The soundbar with subwoofer gets to the root of the problem of unclear vocals and poor sound quality that 2.0 and 2.1 channel soundbars can't solve, allowing you to experience crystal clear sound and unparalleled detail, creating a truly immersive, high-quality audio experience.
  • Tailor Your Sound Atmosphere - All-in-one remote control with battery included — customizable sound control allows for perfect audio balance through 13 adjustable bass and treble levels, enabling you to fine-tune the sound for deep, powerful bass in action-packed movies or bright, clear treble in your favorite music. Additionally, you can choose from three precisely tuned EQ modes (Music, Movie, and News) to enhance specific audio elements, from dynamic stereo effects to clear vocals.
  • Enjoy Enhanced Thumping Bass for Your Smart TVs - Use our 5.25” wired external subwoofer to enhance your audio experience. Feel the power of deep, resonant bass that will make your room vibrate. By handling low-frequency workloads, the subwoofer can protect your main speakers and improve their overall performance. Immerse yourself in the rich, powerful sound that only an external subwoofer can deliver.
  • Continuous Firmware Upgrades - Hiwill is committed to providing users with continuous firmware updates to ensure that your device is always in the best condition. Our team regularly releases updates to fix known issues, improve performance, and introduce new features. You can easily get the latest version and enjoy a smoother experience. We understand your needs, so we always keep optimizing and upgrading the firmware to help you get a better technical experience.
  • Upgraded HDMI eARC/ARC Connections - Support of Using TV remote to control the soundbar in HDMI eARC/ARC mode, no need to use 2 remotes of turning on/off soundbar and tvs. Easily delivers rich, high-definition sound. eARC guarantees seamless audio-video synchronization, providing clear sound that perfectly matches the picture. The TV sound bar also supports Bluetooth, fiber optics and AUX input, ensuring compatibility with older devices.
  • Included Every Thing - All cables, even remote control battery. Package list: Sound bar, Subwoofer, Remote Control, Power Adaptor, HDMI-eARC/Optical/3.5mm audio cables for seamless connectivity. You’re backed by our lifetime friendly customer service.

Product Description

Elevate Every Moment With Dolby Atmos

Transform your living room into a home theater with the Hiwill HiElite A21 soundbar. Bring every scene and music to life, with ultra-precise spatial audio with Dolby Atmos, superior materials and Hiwill HarmonicX Sound Processing (HXS-Processing).

3D Spatial Audio with Dolby Atmos

Dolby Atmos utilizes a unique object-based audio technology to achieve precise sound positioning in three-dimensional space for a highly immersive spatial audio experience, and Hiwill HarmonicX Sound Processing (HXS-Processing) to enhance vocal clarity and refine every sound detail.

Specializing in Dolby Atmos

Experience theater-like sound from your favorite content with Dolby Atmos. This technology offers an immersive three-dimensional sound experience that transcends traditional surround sound systems, delivering depth and clarity that places you at the center of the action

Previous page
Next page

Higher-grade Materials for the Extraordinary

Iconic Copper Ring. Signature High-quality Sound.

Hiwill has specifically added a high-quality copper ring to each driver, enhancing audio clarity by reducing distortion and stabilizing the magnetic field. It delivers deeper bass, crisper highs, and a wider dynamic range, ensuring precise, natural sound for an immersive audio experience.

Aluminum-magnesium Alloy. Rebalance Acoustics.

Crafted with aluminum-magnesium alloy diaphragms, all drivers reduce distortion and latency, delivering exceptional clarity and dynamic range. They offer 20% deeper bass and 30% clearer highs compared to most soundbars using traditional paper diaphragms creating a rich, immersive audio experience.

Tailor Your Sound Atmosphere

Achieve perfect audio balance with 13 customizable bass and treble levels, allowing you to fine-tune your sound for deep, powerful bass in a dynamic movie or bright, clear treble in your favorite music.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • Pajami
      4.0 out of 5 stars Sound is ok - LEDs too bright and default volume is too loud.
      Reviewed in the United States on February 23, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      Update:
      I installed the new firmware, and now the LED in the front isn't as bright and it now remembers the volume. This is a great improvement. I had to grab a USB stick copy the firmware to it and upload via the usb port in the back, which took only a couple minutes.

      bumping this up a star. from 3 to 4
      ********
      I have a budget tv that has fairly poor audio. I wanted to get a sound bar to hopefully improve the viewing experience. Another reason is the rear facing speakers on my tv is towards my kids bedroom and i don't want them to hear the tv while trying to sleep.

      This sound bar is 16.5" x 4.4" x 2.5" the sub woofer is 9" x 12" x 5.25". The sub woofer cable is 5' 8" long and is attached to the unit so you cant replace the wire. It comes with an HDMI cable, a HDMI 90 degree adapter, optical cable, AUX cable, remote & batteries and mounting screws.
      The unit takes optical, hdmi arc, aux, usb and bluetooth in. I only tried it on my tv using optical and HDMI arc.
      First, the sounds is better than the speakers on my TCL 55S515 but that is setting the bar low. Unfortunately this tv doesn't have a lip sync function and its just a little but off, but i'm not going to blame the sounds bar for this.
      There are a few things about this is not great. First, the LEDs on the front are very bright and there is no ability to dim them. This might not be bad in a living room, but in my bed room its noticeable and is distracting.
      Another thing is that the sub woofer wire is short and can't be replaced. The cable just needs to be longer, or replaceable so i can place the sub exactly where i want it.
      The default sound volume is incredibly loud. I think it defaults to 14 and i listen to it at 6.

      i'm debating if its more trouble than its worth.

    • EvilBastard
      4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install and use, rather decent sound quality; controls a little wonky
      Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      The sound quality is pretty decent overall. There's no hissing or audible nose or distortions, and that's all for the good. The unit can get fairly loud, too. Bass is pretty decent, at least when the unit is set to its surround mode.
      Mine was a breeze to set up; I didn't have to refer to the instructions really at all. Using the unit, though, proved a tad bit problematic afterward. The soundbar doesn't remember some settings, for instance. If you set it to, say, Bluetooth and turn it off and then on, it will default to its ARC input. Also, it will lose whatever audio settings you had just set it at. If you had just set its bass level to 6, for instance, that will come back at level 1. It does this kind of thing no matter what. There is a way around this issue, though: just leave your unit on. It will go to sleep by itself and come back without any problems.
      A feature I like but isn't discussed in the documentation: the usb input. I was able to slap in a flash drive with mp3 music files recorded on it, and the unit started playing no problem. I did notice a discrepancy in the unit's volume when you change inputs, though: the volume jumps up somewhat dramatically whenever you change to the usb input.
      One more thing: the controls on the remote are just a tad bit wonky. The input button won't allow you to actually change inputs for instance; it will only allow you to change the settings of whatever input you've previously selected. No, to change the input you have to push on the little button marked movie. The button marked music actually switches the unit's surround mode on and off. (The surround setting is pretty decent on this unit.) The button marked news allows you to select from three different audio modes, news, movies, and music.
      Bluetooth connects right away if it is set up right. I did have a problem one time, though, with no sound coming out even though a connection had been made. I just had to unpair and re-pair after that to make things work okay. There's a delay after you turn the unit on, too.
      Overall, this would be a good little unit to get. It has lots of inputs and thus has lots of flexibility. The sound quality is decent enough. It has some minor issues, but those aren't a dealbreaker.

    • WIFL
      5.0 out of 5 stars Enhance your sound
      Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      I have yet to own a TV that has decent speakers. Sound systems, Surround sound systems, and sound bars, 5.1, 7.4.2, 2.1 or 13.2 the list could go on. All the choices comes down to 2 things really if you ask me, can the room support it and how much you want to spend. After that, its can YOU hear the difference? What is the purpose for upgrading? i have owned a lot of setups and I had recently been doing some remodeling at my house and wanted to improve the sound in the kitchen. This set up was perfect. I didnt want a huge sound bar thats 40 plus inches long but wanted a dedicated "sub-woofer" for the lows. Now this is a 200 watt peak sound bar and has a 5.25" "sub-woofer". We all know that wont be able to shake the pictures off the walls but being in a dedicated box helps. Whats nice is this comes with optical, hdmi, and aux cables. Batteries for the remote and a power cord. You can choose your audio input, i went with the optical.

      The sound is surprising good, huge improvement over the Samsung tv speakers. You can control this from the sound bar its self or the remote. It has a few preset sound choices like movie and music. It also has dedicated treble and bass buttons. It supports Dolby atmos which for this price is nice. Having a sound bar really makes the dialog and all the other tiny sounds of movies come to life. Music plays even a bigger part in my life then movies and you can pair your phone by Bluetooth and play your music through it. Great to do while cleaning. I could go on and on about everything this sound bar can do but If you are wanting a great basic, non intrusive, sound enhancing, sound bar this is definitely one you should look at.
